definitions.definition: To take care of oneself; to take responsibility for one's own well-being.
To defend , to take care of ( typically construed with for ); to block or push away ( typically construed with off ).

main_definition: ( intransitive ) To take care of oneself; to take responsibility for one's own well-being.
secondary_definitions: ( rare , except as "fend for oneself" ) To defend , to take care of ( typically construed with for ); to block or push away ( typically construed with off ).
